Package: unfurl
Version: 0.4.3
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Alienkrishn [Anon4You]
Depends: git, golang
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/tomnomnom/unfurl
Description: Pull out bits of URLs provided on stdin
 unfurl is a command‑line tool that extracts specific components
 (scheme, domain, path, query parameters, etc.) from URLs passed
 via standard input. It is useful for URL parsing and manipulation
 in security testing and data processing pipelines.
